Two specimens from Santa Cruz, Bolivia, and one from Junin , Peru have a complete lateral submarginal pronotal stria, and have pronotal microsculpture (like
P. rudis
), but have sparser dorsal sculpturing and an unbroken anterior marginal pronotal stria, so are ambiguous. We place these here for now, but additional material will be necessary to fully assess patterns of character variation. Specimens from Suriname have the lateral submarginal pronotal stria almost absent, represented by only a very short arc in the anterior corners.
